        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 3:44AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 344 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Porum, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Kanima...                         Porum...
Stigler...                        Briartown...
Enterprise...                     Whitefield...
Gore...                           Tamaha...
Webbers Falls...

This includes Interstate 40 in Oklahoma between mile markers 277 and
294.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT for
southeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
